A N A C T
RELATING TO MOTOR AND OTHER VEHICLES -- MOTOR VEHICLE OFFENSES
Introduced By: Senators Raptakis, Tikoian, Patalano, Appollonio, and Burke
Date Introduced: February 26, 2025
Referred To: Senate Judiciary
It is enacted by the General Assembly as follows:
1 SECTION 1. Section 31-27-4.1 of the General Laws in Chapter 31-27 entitled "Motor
2 Vehicle Offenses" is hereby amended to read as follows:
3 31-27-4.1. Eluding a law enforcement officer with a motor vehicle in a high speed
4 pursuit.
5 Any person who in an attempt to elude or flee from a police officer in an emergency police
6 vehicle in a high speed pursuit of the person, operates a motor vehicle at speeds greater than fifteen
7 (15) miles per hour over the speed limit, or who causes property damage only in excess of one
8 thousand dollars ($1,000) shall, upon conviction, be guilty of a felony and shall be imprisoned for
9 not more than five (5) years at the adult correctional institutions (ACI), and/or be subject to a fine
10 of not less than five thousand dollars ($5,000), but not more than ten thousand dollars ($10,000),
11 and may have their license suspended for not less than one year, but not more than two (2) years,
12 may be subject to the forfeiture of the motor vehicle.:
13 (1) For the first conviction, may be subject to the following sanctions:
14 (i) Up to one year incarceration at the adult correction institutions (A.C.I.) and a fine of
15 five hundred dollars ($500) but not more than one thousand dollars ($1,000);
16 (ii) License suspension of not less than ninety (90) days but not more than six (6) months
17 and forfeiture of the motor vehicle.
18 (2) For a second or subsequent conviction, the person shall:
19 (i) Be sentenced to two (2) years at the A.C.I., but not more than five (5) years;

1 (ii) Be fined a fine of two thousand dollars ($2,000) but not more than five thousand dollars
2 ($5,000);
3 (iii) Receive a license suspension of not less than one year but not more than five (5) years;
4 and
5 (iv) Forfeit the motor vehicle.
6 SECTION 2. This act shall take effect upon passage.
