EXPLANATION
BY THE LEGISLATIVE COUNCIL
OF
A N A C T
RELATING TO MOTOR AND OTHER VEHICLES -- MOTOR VEHICLE OFFENSES
***
1 This act would increase the penalty for anyone found guilty of eluding a police vehicle in
2 high speed pursuit to a felony punishable by up to five (5) years imprisonment, a fine of between
3 five thousand dollars ($5,000) and ten thousand dollars ($10,000), a loss of license from one to two
4 (2) years, and a possible forfeiture of their motor vehicle.
5 This act would take effect upon passage.
